agentBuild.name: agentBuild
agentBuild.description: Compilation time and date of agent program

agentWriteAllowed.name: agentWriteAllowed
agentWriteAllowed.description: Defines whether writable objects can be written (except shutdown/power-off operations)

agentShutdownAllowed.name: agentShutdownAllowed
agentShutdownAllowed.description: Defines whether shutdown/power-off objects can be written

temperatureSensorsTable.name: temperatureSensorsTable
temperatureSensorsTable.description: Table with data of all configured temperature sensors

tempCabinetId.name: tempCabinetId
tempCabinetId.description: ID of the cabinet the temperature sensor is in (index, 0 based)

tempSensorNumber.name: tempSensorNumber
tempSensorNumber.description: Number of the sensor in this cabinet (index, 0 based)

tempSensorStatus.name: tempSensorStatus
tempSensorStatus.description: Status of this temperature sensor (OK, critical or shutdown temperature reached...). The cold and the damage temperature status levels are no longer supported (values 6, 8, 9, 10). Status not-available(99) can be a sensor of a cpu that is not installed. Status sensor-disabled(2) is currently not used.

tempSensorPurpose.name: tempSensorPurpose
tempSensorPurpose.description: Purpose of this temperature sensor (CPU, ambient, housing...). Purposes disable(2) and not-available(6) are no longer used.

tempLowerWarningLevel.name: tempLowerWarningLevel
tempLowerWarningLevel.description: Object made obsolete - no longer supported

tempUpperWarningLevel.name: tempUpperWarningLevel
tempUpperWarningLevel.description: System sends a temperature warning when temperature rises ABOVE this level (degrees Celsius)

tempLowerCriticalLevel.name: tempLowerCriticalLevel
tempLowerCriticalLevel.description: Object made obsolete - no longer supported

tempUpperCriticalLevel.name: tempUpperCriticalLevel
tempUpperCriticalLevel.description: System becomes critical when temperature rises ABOVE this level (degrees Celsius). A system shutdown is performed if object tempCriticalReaction is set to shutdown-and-poweroff.

tempLowerDamageLevel.name: tempLowerDamageLevel
tempLowerDamageLevel.description: Object made obsolete - no longer supported

tempUpperDamageLevel.name: tempUpperDamageLevel
tempUpperDamageLevel.description: Object made obsolete - no longer supported

tempCurrentValue.name: tempCurrentValue
tempCurrentValue.description: Current temperature value (degrees Celsius; -1: unknown temperature, problem with sensor, see tempSensorStatus)

tempCriticalReaction.name: tempCriticalReaction
tempCriticalReaction.description: Reaction when a temperature gets critical (shutdown and power-off, continue...). The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

tempSensorDesignation.name: tempSensorDesignation
tempSensorDesignation.description: String describing the purpose of each temperature sensor in a housing (e.g. CPU, ambient,...). This object will substitute the tempSensorPurpose object.

fansTable.name: fansTable
fansTable.description: Table with data of all configured cooling devices (fans)

fanCabinetId.name: fanCabinetId
fanCabinetId.description: ID of the cabinet the cooling device (fan) is in (index, 0 based)

fanNumber.name: fanNumber
fanNumber.description: Number of the fan in this cabinet (index, 0 based)

fanStatus.name: fanStatus
fanStatus.description: Status of this fan (OK, failed...). Status disabled(2) is no longer used. Status prefailure-predicted(5) means the fan will fail in near future. Status redundant-fan-failed(6) means a redundant fan has failed, the system is not yet critical. Status not-manageable(7) is a fan that is available but has no management facilities. Status not-present(8) can be a hot-plug fan that is currently removed.

fanPurpose.name: fanPurpose
fanPurpose.description: Purpose of this fan (housing, component, CPU on-chip, power supply...). Purpose disabled(2) is currently not used.

fanPositionX.name: fanPositionX
fanPositionX.description: Fax X position - obsolete; for fan indentifying use fanIdentification object

fanPositionY.name: fanPositionY
fanPositionY.description: Fax Y position - obsolete; for fan indentifying use fanIdentification object

fanPositionZ.name: fanPositionZ
fanPositionZ.description: Fax Z position - obsolete; for fan indentifying use fanIdentification object

fanCurrentSpeed.name: fanCurrentSpeed
fanCurrentSpeed.description: Current speed of the fan (in revolutions per minute, -1 = unknown)

fanNominalMaximumSpeed.name: fanNominalMaximumSpeed
fanNominalMaximumSpeed.description: Nominal speed of the fan (in revolutions per minute) on maximum power; the speed is measured the first time the agent is installed and than compared daily to the current speed on maximum power to detect a fan prefailure (-1 = unknown).

fanCurrentMaximumSpeed.name: fanCurrentMaximumSpeed
fanCurrentMaximumSpeed.description: Current speed of the fan (in revolutions per minute) on maximum power (-1 = unknown).

fanFailReaction.name: fanFailReaction
fanFailReaction.description: Reaction when a fan has failed (shutdown and power-off, continue...). The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

fanFailShutdownDelay.name: fanFailShutdownDelay
fanFailShutdownDelay.description: Delay time (in seconds) when shutdown should commit on fan fail (if shutdown-and-off is configured, 0 = immediately, -1 = unknown). The value unknown(-1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

fanDesignation.name: fanDesignation
fanDesignation.description: String describing the purpose of each fan in a housing (e.g. CPU, Power Supply,...). This object will substitute the fanPurpose object.

fanIdentification.name: fanIdentification
fanIdentification.description: String identifying each fan in a housing (e.g. CPU0, CPU1, PS0...)

fanDailyTestTime.name: fanDailyTestTime
fanDailyTestTime.description: Daily time when to automatically test fan speeds (in minutes since midnight; -1 = unknown, automatic fan test not supported). The value unknown(-1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

fanStartTest.name: fanStartTest
fanStartTest.description: Start test of all fans to get the speed at maximum power (this test is normally started automatically once a day). Reading this object just returns the value 0.

eventLogTable.name: eventLogTable
eventLogTable.description: Table with event log entries (can also contain critical errors when an ErrorLog for critical errors is not available)

eventLogMessageData.name: eventLogMessageData
eventLogMessageData.description: Non-critical message log entry as described above

eventLogMaxEntries.name: eventLogMaxEntries
eventLogMaxEntries.description: Number of EventLog entries (can be used to directly get all table entries with one varbind list)

errorLogTable.name: errorLogTable
errorLogTable.description: Table with major and critial error log entries (can be missing on some hardware platforms)

errorLogEntryNumber.name: errorLogEntryNumber
errorLogEntryNumber.description: Entry number in critical errorLogTable (index, 0 based)

errorLogMessageData.name: errorLogMessageData
errorLogMessageData.description: Major/critical message log entry as described above

errorLogMaxEntries.name: errorLogMaxEntries
errorLogMaxEntries.description: Number of ErrorLog entries (can be used to directly get all table entries with one varbind list)

hardwareWatchdogStatus.name: hardwareWatchdogStatus
hardwareWatchdogStatus.description: Status of the hardware watchdog (periodically restarted by the server management BIOS). The hardware watchdog is only supported on SMI based management hardware, not for micro controller hardware.

hardwareWatchdogTime.name: hardwareWatchdogTime
hardwareWatchdogTime.description: Timeout time of the hardware watchdog (in seconds, -1 = unknown)

hardwareWatchdogEnable.name: hardwareWatchdogEnable
hardwareWatchdogEnable.description: Enable/disable the hardware watchdog. The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

softwareWatchdogStatus.name: softwareWatchdogStatus
softwareWatchdogStatus.description: Status of the software watchdog (periodically restarted by the server management agent)

softwareWatchdogTime.name: softwareWatchdogTime
softwareWatchdogTime.description: Timeout time of the software watchdog (in minutes, -1 = unknown). The value unknown(-1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

softwareWatchdogEnable.name: softwareWatchdogEnable
softwareWatchdogEnable.description: Enable/disable the software watchdog. The value unknown(-1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

softwareWatchdogAction.name: softwareWatchdogAction
softwareWatchdogAction.description: Behavior when the software watchdog timeout occurs (reboot, continue...). This value is only used if the watchdog is enabled. If set to continue and the watchdog has timeout, it will only be logged and no reset happens. The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

bootWatchdogStatus.name: bootWatchdogStatus
bootWatchdogStatus.description: Status of the boot watchdog (started at system boot, reset by the server management agent). If the SC agent is not started within the specified time, the management controller assumes the system did not boot correctly and executes system reboot.

bootWatchdogTime.name: bootWatchdogTime
bootWatchdogTime.description: Timeout time of the boot watchdog (in minutes, -1 = unknown). The value unknown(-1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

bootWatchdogEnable.name: bootWatchdogEnable
bootWatchdogEnable.description: Enable/disable the boot watchdog. The value unknown(-1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

bootWatchdogAction.name: bootWatchdogAction
bootWatchdogAction.description: Behavior when the boot watchdog timeout occurs (reboot, continue...). This value is only used if the watchdog is enabled. If set to continue and the watchdog has timeout, it will only be logged and no reset happens. The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

cpuTableIndex.name: cpuTableIndex
cpuTableIndex.description: Number of the CPU in the CpuTable (index, 0 based)

cpuType.name: cpuType
cpuType.description: Type of the CPU (486, Pentium, R2000...)

cpuFrequency.name: cpuFrequency
cpuFrequency.description: Frequency of the CPU (in MHz, -1 = unknown)

cpuStatus.name: cpuStatus
cpuStatus.description: Status of a CPU: unknown(1) : CPU status could not be evaluated disabled(2) : CPU was manually disabled in BIOS setup ok(3) : CPU is available and operating properly not-present(4) : CPU is not available, empty socket error(5) : CPU has encountered errors but is still in use fail(6) : CPU has failed and is disabled missing-termination(7): CPU socket needs a terminator module when not populated but the terminator is missing prefailure-warning(8) : CPU has too many correctable errors within a certain time period

cpuName.name: cpuName
cpuName.description: Name of the CPU (e.g. 'Pentium', 'Pentium Pro' ...) as text string

cpuSocketDesignation.name: cpuSocketDesignation
cpuSocketDesignation.description: String containing the socket designation of a CPU. This is the same text that is written on the system board.

cpuNrLogicalsPerPhysical.name: cpuNrLogicalsPerPhysical
cpuNrLogicalsPerPhysical.description: Number of logical CPUs within one physical CPU (for hyper-threading and multi-core CPUs). This is the sum of all cores and all logical CPUs of a hyper-threading CPU.

cpuCacheL1Size.name: cpuCacheL1Size
cpuCacheL1Size.description: Level 1 cache size (kByte) of a physical CPU (0 if unknown or not available).

cpuCacheL2Size.name: cpuCacheL2Size
cpuCacheL2Size.description: Level 2 cache size (kByte) of a physical CPU (0 if unknown or not available).

cpuCacheL3Size.name: cpuCacheL3Size
cpuCacheL3Size.description: Level 3 cache size (kByte) of a physical CPU (0 if unknown or not available).

cpuNrCoresPerPhysical.name: cpuNrCoresPerPhysical
cpuNrCoresPerPhysical.description: Number of cores within one physical CPU (for multi-core CPUs).

secondLevelCacheSize.name: secondLevelCacheSize
secondLevelCacheSize.description: Size of the second level cache (in kBytes, 0 if not available or disabled, -1 = unknown). Object will be made obsolete in next releases; use cpuCacheL2Size instead!

secondLevelCacheWritePolicy.name: secondLevelCacheWritePolicy
secondLevelCacheWritePolicy.description: Write policy of the second level cache (write-back, write-through). Object will be made obsolete in next releases (no longer required).

physicalMemorySize.name: physicalMemorySize
physicalMemorySize.description: Size of the whole physical memory on the system board (in MBytes, -1 = unknown)

baseMemorySize.name: baseMemorySize
baseMemorySize.description: Size of the base memory (below 1 MB) on the system board (in kBytes, -1 = unknown)

extendedMemorySize.name: extendedMemorySize
extendedMemorySize.description: Size of the extended memory (above 1 MB) on the system board (in MBytes, -1 = unknown)

utilizationMethod.name: utilizationMethod
utilizationMethod.description: Method to get utilization values: take-snapshot-now: get all values and store them to have all values at one certain time (set this object each time you want to get new values) get-current-values (default): get the values directly without buffering. The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

utilizationPciLoad.name: utilizationPciLoad
utilizationPciLoad.description: Load on the PCI bus (in percent; -1 if unknown); do no longer use this object for new implementations; object replaced by pciUtilizationTable.

utilizationEisaLoad.name: utilizationEisaLoad
utilizationEisaLoad.description: Load on the EISA bus (in percent; -1 if unknown)

memModuleBank.name: memModuleBank
memModuleBank.description: Bank number the module belongs to (-1 = unknown).

memModuleStatus.name: memModuleStatus
memModuleStatus.description: Status of the memory module socket (OK, fail, disabled...). unknown(1) : module status could not be evaluated error(2) : module has encountered errors but is still in use ok(3) : module is available and operating properly not-available(4) : empty socket, module is not available fail(5) : module has failed and is disabled prefailure-warning(6) : module has too many correctable errors within a certain time period hot-space(7) : module is a hot-spare (standby) module, which can be used as a run-time-replacement for failed modules mirror(8) : module is part of a mirror disabled(9) : module was manually disabled in BIOS setup raid(10) : module is part of a memory module RAID system

memModuleErrors.name: memModuleErrors
memModuleErrors.description: Number of (parity) errors in this module since last error count reset (-1 = unknown)

memModuleStartAddress.name: memModuleStartAddress
memModuleStartAddress.description: Start address of the bank this memory belongs to (-1 = unknown). This object is obsolete when the main memory size exceeds 2 GByte. Use new object memModuleStartAddressMB instead.

memModuleSize.name: memModuleSize
memModuleSize.description: Size of this memory module (in bytes, -1 = unknown). This object is obsolete when the module's size exceeds 2 GByte. Use new object memModuleSizeMB instead.

memModuleType.name: memModuleType
memModuleType.description: Type of memory module (Parity, NoParity, ECD, EDO...). Will be made obsolete in next agent releases!!! Use memModuleType2 for newer implementations!

memModuleType2.name: memModuleType2
memModuleType2.description: Information about the type of a memory module (Parity, ECC, EDO, SIMM, DIMM...). The type is a combination of one or more bits. Bit field: Bit 0 - Other Bit 1 - Unknown Bit 2 - Standard Bit 3 - Fast page mode Bit 4 - EDO Bit 5 - Parity Bit 6 - ECC Bit 7 - SIMM Bit 8 - DIMM Bit 9 - RIMM Unused bits are set to zero.

memModuleSocketDesignation.name: memModuleSocketDesignation
memModuleSocketDesignation.description: String containing the socket designation of a memory module. This is the same text that is written on the system board.

memModuleCorrectableErrors.name: memModuleCorrectableErrors
memModuleCorrectableErrors.description: Number of correctable errors in this module since last error count reset (-1 = unknown)

memModuleApproved.name: memModuleApproved
memModuleApproved.description: Information whether the memory module has been approved by the system vendor. unknown(1) is given when a module is not available or module cannot be accessed; no(2) when no approval information is found; yes(3) when a valid approval information is found in the module.

memModuleStartAddressMB.name: memModuleStartAddressMB
memModuleStartAddressMB.description: Start address (in MBytes) of the bank this memory belongs to (-1 = unknown). This object makes the object memModuleStartAddress obsolete (4 GByte limit).

memModuleSizeMB.name: memModuleSizeMB
memModuleSizeMB.description: Size (in MBytes) of this memory module (-1 = unknown). This object makes the object memModuleSize obsolete (4 GByte limit).

memoryErrorCounterReset.name: memoryErrorCounterReset
memoryErrorCounterReset.description: Reset the memory module error counters (and set a new start time), reading this object just returns the value 0.

memoryErrorCounterStartTime.name: memoryErrorCounterStartTime
memoryErrorCounterStartTime.description: Time when memory module error counters were started (seconds since 1/1/1970, -1 = unknown)

pciUtilizationTable.name: pciUtilizationTable
pciUtilizationTable.description: Table with PCI bus utilization data; independent of utilizationMethod object, update method for this table is always get-current-values. The number of entries in this table can be read from MIB object sniScNumberPciBusses.

pciUtilBusLoad.name: pciUtilBusLoad
pciUtilBusLoad.description: PCI bus load (in percent, 0xffffffff if unknown)

pciUtilBusTransferRate.name: pciUtilBusTransferRate
pciUtilBusTransferRate.description: PCI bus data transfer rate (in MBytes/second, 0xffffffff if unknown)

pciUtilBusEfficiency.name: pciUtilBusEfficiency
pciUtilBusEfficiency.description: PCI bus efficiency, ratio of data transfer rate through bus load (in percent); avarage value over all devices on this PCI bus; optimum value is 100 percent (0xffffffff if unknown).

sniScBiosVersionString.name: sniScBiosVersionString
sniScBiosVersionString.description: String containing complete BIOS version, e.g. V4.05 R1.03.887

sniScNumberCpuSockets.name: sniScNumberCpuSockets
sniScNumberCpuSockets.description: Number of CPU sockets available on the system board. This is not the number of currently installed CPUs! This object also describes the number of entries in the 'cpuTable' (-1 = unknown).

sniScNumberMemoryModules.name: sniScNumberMemoryModules
sniScNumberMemoryModules.description: Number of memory module sockets available on the system board (or memory extension board). This is not the number of currently installed memory modules! This object also describes the number of entries in the 'memoryModulesTable' (-1 = unknown).

sniScNumberPciBusses.name: sniScNumberPciBusses
sniScNumberPciBusses.description: Number of PCI busses available in the system (-1 = unknown).

totalMemoryUsage.name: totalMemoryUsage
totalMemoryUsage.description: Total system memory usage (virtual and physical, in KBytes, -1 = unknown)

totalMemoryUsagePercent.name: totalMemoryUsagePercent
totalMemoryUsagePercent.description: Total system memory usage (virtual and physical, in percent, -1 = unknown)

physicalMemoryUsage.name: physicalMemoryUsage
physicalMemoryUsage.description: Physical system memory usage (in KBytes, -1 = unknown)

physicalMemoryUsagePercent.name: physicalMemoryUsagePercent
physicalMemoryUsagePercent.description: Physical system memory usage (in percent, -1 = unknown)

totalMemoryAvailable.name: totalMemoryAvailable
totalMemoryAvailable.description: Total system memory available (virtual and physical, in KBytes, -1 = unknown)

physicalMemoryAvailable.name: physicalMemoryAvailable
physicalMemoryAvailable.description: Physical system memory available (in KBytes, -1 = unknown)

physicalMemoryOsSize.name: physicalMemoryOsSize
physicalMemoryOsSize.description: Total size of the whole physical memory available to the operating system; this value is similar to 'physicalMemorySize', but may be less if the system has mirror or hot spare memory modules (in MBytes, -1 = unknown)

pagerUserTable.name: pagerUserTable
pagerUserTable.description: Table with info of the users that should be paged

pagerUserIndex.name: pagerUserIndex
pagerUserIndex.description: Index into pager user table (0 based)

pagerType.name: pagerType
pagerType.description: Type of the installed pager (signal, numeric, alfa-numeric). The value unknown(1) and not-available(2) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

pagerUserDescription.name: pagerUserDescription
pagerUserDescription.description: Description (function, optional) of the pager user

pagerActive.name: pagerActive
pagerActive.description: Describes whether this pager is active and should be called. The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

pagerNumber.name: pagerNumber
pagerNumber.description: User ID number of the user's pager

pagerServiceProviderNumber.name: pagerServiceProviderNumber
pagerServiceProviderNumber.description: Telephone dial number of the pager service provider (can also contain additional modem dial characters)

pagerActivityPrompt.name: pagerActivityPrompt
pagerActivityPrompt.description: Prompt string that should be received before pager number can be sent

pagerTimeModel.name: pagerTimeModel
pagerTimeModel.description: Encoded string containing a pager time model (when should which user be paged); this value is currently not used.

pagerInitString.name: pagerInitString
pagerInitString.description: Init string that will be sent to the pager modem before the dialing begins

pagerServerNumber.name: pagerServerNumber
pagerServerNumber.description: Number of this server. It is sent together with the error number as a message to the user's pager (-1 = unknown). The value unknown(-1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

pagerComPort.name: pagerComPort
pagerComPort.description: COM port number (1...4) the pager modem is connected to. The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

pagerComPortBaudRate.name: pagerComPortBaudRate
pagerComPortBaudRate.description: Baud rate of the pager COM port. Following values are supported: 1200, 2400, 4800, 9600, 19200 (-1 = unknown). The value unknown(-1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

pagerComPortParity.name: pagerComPortParity
pagerComPortParity.description: Parity check configuration for the pager COM port. The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

pagerComPortNumBits.name: pagerComPortNumBits
pagerComPortNumBits.description: Number of bits per byte on the pager COM port (7, 8, -1 = unknown). The value unknown(-1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

pagerComPortFlowControl.name: pagerComPortFlowControl
pagerComPortFlowControl.description: Flow control method of the pager COM port (Hardware, XON/XOFF...). The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

pagerModemName.name: pagerModemName
pagerModemName.description: Optional modem name or type; can be used just as info to be displayed.

stdSetupPasswordEnable.name: stdSetupPasswordEnable
stdSetupPasswordEnable.description: Tells whether a password is configured for the standard BIOS (read-only)

stdSetupBootSource.name: stdSetupBootSource
stdSetupBootSource.description: Source medium to boot from: Normal system or diagnostic system standard(2): standard boot diag-system(4): boot from alternate diagnostic system The source the diagnostic system is booted from is selected in object 'srvSetupRebootFailAction'. The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

stdSetupPostErrorHalt.name: stdSetupPostErrorHalt
stdSetupPostErrorHalt.description: Describes what to do when a POST error has occured (halt on any error, no halt on any error...). The values unknown(1) and other(9) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

stdSetupSerialInterface1.name: stdSetupSerialInterface1
stdSetupSerialInterface1.description: The COM port which the on-board serial interface 1 is mapped to (1...4). The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

stdSetupSerialInterface2.name: stdSetupSerialInterface2
stdSetupSerialInterface2.description: The COM port which the on-board serial interface 2 is mapped to (1...4). The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

stdSetupParallelInterface.name: stdSetupParallelInterface
stdSetupParallelInterface.description: The LPT port which the on-board parallel interface is mapped to (1...3). The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

stdSetupFloppyController.name: stdSetupFloppyController
stdSetupFloppyController.description: Describes whether the floppy controller is enabled. The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

stdSetupHarddiskController.name: stdSetupHarddiskController
stdSetupHarddiskController.description: Describes whether the IDE harddisk controller is enabled. The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

stdSetupMouseController.name: stdSetupMouseController
stdSetupMouseController.description: Describes whether the mouse port controller is enabled. The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

srvSetupCabinetId.name: srvSetupCabinetId
srvSetupCabinetId.description: Cabinet ID number of this server (-1 = unknown). The value unknown(-1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'. Use this number as cabinetId for all tables containing a cabinet index. If unknown is delivered, 0 should be used as cabinet index.

srvSetupServerRackSlot.name: srvSetupServerRackSlot
srvSetupServerRackSlot.description: Slot number (in a rack) this server is in (only for rack servers; -1 = unknown). The value unknown(-1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'. This object is currently not used.

srvSetupRemoteOnEnable.name: srvSetupRemoteOnEnable
srvSetupRemoteOnEnable.description: Describes whether remote-on via RI modem line is enabled or not available. The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

srvSetupMaxRestartRetries.name: srvSetupMaxRestartRetries
srvSetupMaxRestartRetries.description: Maximum number of retries to reboot/restart the server when a shutdown (and power-off) had occured. After this number of retries the action defined in 'srvSetupRebootFailAction' will be executed (-1 = unknown, no retries). The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

srvSetupRebootFailAction.name: srvSetupRebootFailAction
srvSetupRebootFailAction.description: Describes the action on a specified number of failed reboot retries (srvSetupMaxRestartRetries=0): unknown(1) - diagnostic system cannot be determined (cannot be SET) switch-off(2) - no diag system, final power-off ide-diag-disk(3) - boot diag system from IDE disk no-diag-system(4) - no diag system available remote-image-disk(5) - boot from remote image (over LAN) pxe(6) - boot from PXE (Preboot eXecution Environment) rsb-usb(7) - boot from RSB remote source (via USB interface) bmc-remote(8) - boot from BMC from remote storage This value is also the source to be booted from when object 'stdSetupBootSource' is set to 'diag-system'.

srvSetupRebootFailPager.name: srvSetupRebootFailPager
srvSetupRebootFailPager.description: Describes whether the pager should be activated when reboot after error shutdown had occured. The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

srvSetupSeGroupNumber.name: srvSetupSeGroupNumber
srvSetupSeGroupNumber.description: Group number for storage extension communication bus. Legal values are 0..9, -1 = unknown. The value unknown(-1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

srvSetupRestartRetriesDefault.name: srvSetupRestartRetriesDefault
srvSetupRestartRetriesDefault.description: Default number of retries to reboot/restart the server when a shutdown (and power-off) had occured. This value will be copied to object srvSetupMaxRestartRetries by the user to reset the counter to its original (default) value (-1 = unknown, no retries). The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

onOffTimesTable.name: onOffTimesTable
onOffTimesTable.description: Table with system power on/off times; power-on will be performed by the real-time clock, power-off (with shutdown) by the operating system (system control service); table must be enabled before using

onOffWeekday.name: onOffWeekday
onOffWeekday.description: Day of the week the times should act upon (index, 1 based); 1 = Sunday, 2 = Monday...

onTime.name: onTime
onTime.description: Time the system should be switched on (by the real-time clock; in minutes since midnight; -1 = disabled, no on time). Only values -1 and 0..1439 are allowed.

offTime.name: offTime
offTime.description: Time the system should be switched off (by the operating system; in minutes since midnight; -1 = disabled, no off time). Only values -1 and 0..1439 are allowed.

shutdownDelayTime.name: shutdownDelayTime
shutdownDelayTime.description: The delay time (in minutes) the agent should wait before executing a shutdown (with doShutdown); 0 = default = shutdown immediately; -1 = unknown. The value unknown(-1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

doShutdown.name: doShutdown
doShutdown.description: Execute a shutdown; argument tells what kind of shutdown: shutdown: wait for user to switch off or reboot shutdown-and-off: switch off after shutdown shutdown-and-reboot: reboot after shutdown abort-pending-shutdown: abort a delayed shutdown immediately (if not already initiated) Reading this object just returns the value 0.

powerOnCounts.name: powerOnCounts
powerOnCounts.description: Tells how often the server was switched on in its life (-1 = unknown)

powerOnDurationHours.name: powerOnDurationHours
powerOnDurationHours.description: Tells how long the system was switched on in its life (in hours; -1 = unknown)

powerOffDurationHours.name: powerOffDurationHours
powerOffDurationHours.description: Tells how long the system was switched off in its life (in hours; -1 = unknown)

errorOffRestartDelay.name: errorOffRestartDelay
errorOffRestartDelay.description: Delay (in minutes) when the system should be automatically switched on again (by real-time clock) after an error power-off (-1 = no switch-on function). The value unknown(-1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'. On some platforms only the values 1, 2, 3, 5, 7, 10, 15 and 20 can be set. Values between these numbers will be rounded.

lastPostStatus.name: lastPostStatus
lastPostStatus.description: Describes whether the last (current) POST (power on self test) was errornous. Object is now obsolete - use object systemBootStatus instead!

lastPowerOffSource.name: lastPowerOffSource
lastPowerOffSource.description: Reason why the system was switched off last time

lastPowerOnSource.name: lastPowerOnSource
lastPowerOnSource.description: Source the system was switched on from

powerOnTime.name: powerOnTime
powerOnTime.description: Time and Date the system was booted (seconds since 1/1/1970; -1 = unknown)

doPowerOnOff.name: doPowerOnOff
doPowerOnOff.description: Switch the server on or off; argument tells what kind of action: on: switch power on off: switch power off power-cycle: switch power off and switch power on again reset: perform a server reset nmi: perform a non-maskable interrupt (NMI, mainly for debugging purpose)

systemBootResult.name: systemBootResult
systemBootResult.description: Result of the last server boot.

systemBootStatus.name: systemBootStatus
systemBootStatus.description: Status of the current boot process.

numberCabinetsConfigured.name: numberCabinetsConfigured
numberCabinetsConfigured.description: Number of configured cabinets (server and storage extensions, at least 1: the server itself)

numberCabinetsDetected.name: numberCabinetsDetected
numberCabinetsDetected.description: Number of detected cabinets (server and storage extensions, at least 1: the server itself). This is also the number of entries in cabinetInfosTable.

cabinetInfosTable.name: cabinetInfosTable
cabinetInfosTable.description: Table with data of all configured cabinets

cabinetId.name: cabinetId
cabinetId.description: Cabinet ID number, index into the cabinet table

cabinetLocation.name: cabinetLocation
cabinetLocation.description: The place where the cabinet is located (user can store any string here to identify the cabinet location)

cabinetIdentNumber.name: cabinetIdentNumber
cabinetIdentNumber.description: System ident number (serial number) - will be a number like 'XYZZ 12345678'. XYZZ is the cabinet identifier and is mandatory. It will be used to identify the cabinet model name (i.e. PCD-5S). 12345678 is the cabinet serial number and is optional. Cabinet identifier and serial number are separated by a blank character!

cabinetNumberFans.name: cabinetNumberFans
cabinetNumberFans.description: The number of configured cooling devices (fans) in this cabinet (-1 = unknown)

cabinetNumberTempSensors.name: cabinetNumberTempSensors
cabinetNumberTempSensors.description: The number of configured temperature sensors in this cabinet (-1 = unknown)

cabinetNumberPowerSupplies.name: cabinetNumberPowerSupplies
cabinetNumberPowerSupplies.description: The number of available power supplies in this cabinet (-1 = unknown)

cabinetPowerSupplySlots.name: cabinetPowerSupplySlots
cabinetPowerSupplySlots.description: The number of power supply slots in this cabinet (is the maximum number of installable power supplies; 0 if no hot-plug slots available; -1 = unknown)

cabinetUpsUsed.name: cabinetUpsUsed
cabinetUpsUsed.description: Uninterruptable power supply for this cabinet available: 0: No UPS 1..n: Index in UPS table -1: unknown

cabinetBoardSerialNumber.name: cabinetBoardSerialNumber
cabinetBoardSerialNumber.description: Serial number of the cabinet's system board

cabinetBoardRevision.name: cabinetBoardRevision
cabinetBoardRevision.description: Revision (GS) of the cabinet's system board (-1 = unknown). Value obsolete, use sieScCabinetBoardRevisionString instead!

cabinetBoardId.name: cabinetBoardId
cabinetBoardId.description: Identifier string of the cabinet's system board

cabinetManagementControllerType.name: cabinetManagementControllerType
cabinetManagementControllerType.description: Type of the cabinet's system management controller (i.e. SNI System Control Board)

cabinetControllerFirmwareMajor.name: cabinetControllerFirmwareMajor
cabinetControllerFirmwareMajor.description: Firmware version (major number) of the cabinet's system management controller (-1 = unknown). This object will be replaced by sieScCabinetControllerFirmware in future versions.

cabinetControllerFirmwareMinor.name: cabinetControllerFirmwareMinor
cabinetControllerFirmwareMinor.description: Firmware version (minor number) of the cabinet's system management controller (-1 = unknown). This object will be replaced by sieScCabinetControllerFirmware in future versions.

cabinetAttribute.name: cabinetAttribute
cabinetAttribute.description: Attribute of a cabinet (Primary/secondary server, storage extension...)

cabinetStatusSummary.name: cabinetStatusSummary
cabinetStatusSummary.description: Describes the status of a cabinet (OK, degraded, error...)

cabinetLastPoweroffSource.name: cabinetLastPoweroffSource
cabinetLastPoweroffSource.description: The source from which the cabinet was powered off last time

cabinetActionAfterAcFail.name: cabinetActionAfterAcFail
cabinetActionAfterAcFail.description: Action on AC power resume after AC has failed. not-available(2) : function not available, behavior is hardware-defined. as-before(3) : server gets the same power state as before the AC fail. remain-off(4) : server remains off on power resume. switch-on(5) : server is always switched on on power resume. The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

cabinetBbuUsed.name: cabinetBbuUsed
cabinetBbuUsed.description: Battery buffering unit for this cabinet available. The value unknown(1) cannot be set, a SET will deliver 'badValue'.

cabinetSystemType.name: cabinetSystemType
cabinetSystemType.description: Value is obsolete. This value should no longer be used for cabinet identification. Use cabinetHousingType to identify the housing type and cabinetSystemName for the type of the cabinet!

cabinetStatusDetail.name: cabinetStatusDetail
cabinetStatusDetail.description: More detailed status information from this cabinet. The StatusDetail object is set to reflect the new status. ok: (status ok) no failures detected. selftestWarning: (status degraded) the SCB firmware issued a warning condition. selftestFailure: (status error) the SCB firmware detected a failure that prevents it from functioning. powerFailure: (status degraded) the AC input at the power supply or the AC input at the UPS failed. fanFailure: (status error) A fan in this cabinet failed. The system is going to shut down. temperatureFailure: (status error) A sensor in this cabinet detected an over temperature. The system is going to shut down. communicationFailure: (status error) The SCB in the CPU cabinet has lost communication with the SCB in this cabinet. The system is going to shut down. powerOff: (status degraded) The cabinet is switched off.

cabinetHousingType.name: cabinetHousingType
cabinetHousingType.description: Type string for cabinet housing type (i.e. 'P300' for all PRIMERGY 3xx housings); this object should be used to identify the cabinet instead of using object cabinetSystemType (i.e. for painting pictures in management applications)

cabinetFrontDoorStatus.name: cabinetFrontDoorStatus
cabinetFrontDoorStatus.description: Status of the cabinet's front door

cabinetHousingOpenStatus.name: cabinetHousingOpenStatus
cabinetHousingOpenStatus.description: Status describing whether the housing is open or closed

sieScCabinetNumberVoltages.name: sieScCabinetNumberVoltages
sieScCabinetNumberVoltages.description: Number of entries in power supply voltage table

sieScCabinetControllerFirmware.name: sieScCabinetControllerFirmware
sieScCabinetControllerFirmware.description: The cabinet's system management controller firmware version (i.e. '1.1.4.88'). This object will replace the previous objects cabinetControllerFirmwareMinor and cabinetControllerFirmwareMajor.

sieScCabinetBoardRevisionString.name: sieScCabinetBoardRevisionString
sieScCabinetBoardRevisionString.description: Revision string (GS, WGS...) of the cabinet's system board. This object replaces the previous object cabinetBoardRevision.

sieScCabinetAdministrativeURL.name: sieScCabinetAdministrativeURL
sieScCabinetAdministrativeURL.description: Provides a URL that may be used by a front-end to start a web browser and connect it directly to the cabinet's administrative web server (e.g. https://10.0.0.2:443/foobar.html).

sieScRemcsId.name: sieScRemcsId
sieScRemcsId.description: REMCS system identification string (binary data): Format of Fujitsu REMCS ID (40byte) Format = TTMMMMMMMMMMMMmmmmmmmmmmmmCCnnnnnnnnnnnn TT : 2byte : Type ID for Company Name MM...M : 12byte : Model Name mm...m : 12byte : Device Name CC : 2byte : Checksum nn...n : 12byte : Serial number

serverType.name: serverType
serverType.description: Value is obsolete. This value should no longer be used for server identification. Use serverHousingType to identify the housing type and cabinetSystemName for the type of the server!

serverHousingType.name: serverHousingType
serverHousingType.description: Type string for cabinet housing type (i.e. 'P300' for all PRIMERGY 3xx housings); this object should be used to identify the cabinet instead of using object serverType (i.e. for painting pictures in management applications). This is the same value as from object cabinetHousingType for the server cabinet.

serverUUID.name: serverUUID
serverUUID.description: Universal Unique ID (UUID) number - this is a world wide unique ID number of the server. Can be used for identifying a server. This UUID is formatted as specified in RFC 4122; shown in network byte order (big-endian). For little-endian format please use the SC2.MIB object sc2srvUUIDWireFormat! The UUID string format is like this: 157E465A-A4AC-D711-A847-DD85CECD12EC

powerSuppliesTable.name: powerSuppliesTable
powerSuppliesTable.description: Table with power supply groups in the cabinets

powerSupplyCabinetId.name: powerSupplyCabinetId
powerSupplyCabinetId.description: Cabinet ID, index into the power supply table (0 based)

powerSupplyStatus.name: powerSupplyStatus
powerSupplyStatus.description: Status of the cabinet's power supply group; ok: all units OK, number >= minimum degraded: one or more units failed, number OK >= minimum critical: number OK < minimum.

powerSupplyRedundancy.name: powerSupplyRedundancy
powerSupplyRedundancy.description: Number of available redundant power supply units (i.e. 2 units minimum, 3 available -> redundancy is 1, -1 = unknown)

powerSupplyUnitsTable.name: powerSupplyUnitsTable
powerSupplyUnitsTable.description: Table with info about the configured power supply units

powerSupplyUnitCabinetId.name: powerSupplyUnitCabinetId
powerSupplyUnitCabinetId.description: Cabinet ID, index into the power supply unit table (0 based)

powerSupplyUnitNumber.name: powerSupplyUnitNumber
powerSupplyUnitNumber.description: Power supply unit number, index into power supply unit table (0 based)

powerSupplyUnitStatus.name: powerSupplyUnitStatus
powerSupplyUnitStatus.description: Status of the power supply unit (OK, failed, not present...)

powerSupplyUnitDesignation.name: powerSupplyUnitDesignation
powerSupplyUnitDesignation.description: Power supply unit designation. This string specifies a name/designation for the power supply unit. The designation string may not be available on some platforms.

sniScVoltageTable.name: sniScVoltageTable
sniScVoltageTable.description: Table with power supply voltage information

sniScVoltageCabinetNumber.name: sniScVoltageCabinetNumber
sniScVoltageCabinetNumber.description: Cabinet number, index into the power supply voltage table (0 based)

sniScVoltageNumber.name: sniScVoltageNumber
sniScVoltageNumber.description: Power supply voltage number, index into power supply voltage table (0 based)

sniScVoltageStatus.name: sniScVoltageStatus
sniScVoltageStatus.description: Status of the power supply voltage; 'not-available' maybe the voltage of an empty CPU socket; 'out-of-range' comes when the voltage is out of range; 'prefailure' is used for battery voltages and informs that the battery is predicted to fail in near future.

sniScVoltageDesignation.name: sniScVoltageDesignation
sniScVoltageDesignation.description: Power supply voltage designation. This string specifies the voltage by clear text (e.g. 5V, 12V, 3.3V...)

sniScVoltageMinimumValue.name: sniScVoltageMinimumValue
sniScVoltageMinimumValue.description: Power supply voltage minimum level (1/100th Volts; -1 = unknown)

sniScVoltageMaximumValue.name: sniScVoltageMaximumValue
sniScVoltageMaximumValue.description: Power supply voltage maximum level (1/100th Volts; -1 = unknown)

sniScVoltageCurrentValue.name: sniScVoltageCurrentValue
sniScVoltageCurrentValue.description: Power supply voltage current level, negative voltages are reported as negative values (1/100th Volts, e.g. 330 means 3.30 Volts; -177 (0xFFFFFF4F) means -1.77 Volts; 0xFFFFFFFF = unknown)

sniScVoltageNominalValue.name: sniScVoltageNominalValue
sniScVoltageNominalValue.description: Power supply voltage nominal level (1/100th Volts; -1 = unknown)

sniScVoltageOutputLoad.name: sniScVoltageOutputLoad
sniScVoltageOutputLoad.description: Power supply output load in percent of maximum load; 0xFFFFFFFF = unknown

upsCount.name: upsCount
upsCount.description: Number of uninterruptable power supplies (UPS) in this system (-1 = unknown)

upsInfosTable.name: upsInfosTable
upsInfosTable.description: Table with uninterruptable power supplies used in this system. The index is the UPS number used in the system. One or more server or storage-extension objects can reference to a UPS entry in this table.

upsNumber.name: upsNumber
upsNumber.description: Number of the UPS in this table (index, 1 based)

upsDetected.name: upsDetected
upsDetected.description: Tells whether the UPS was detected

upsDischargeTime.name: upsDischargeTime
upsDischargeTime.description: Maximum time this UPS will be discharged, after that a shutdown will be performed (seconds; -1 = unknown)

upsType.name: upsType
upsType.description: Type of the UPS; can be used to identify an OEM UPS with an OEM agent

upsOemAgent.name: upsOemAgent
upsOemAgent.description: Object identifier of an OEM UPS MIB; no agent if empty OID

upsOemAgentAddress.name: upsOemAgentAddress
upsOemAgentAddress.description: IP address of an OEM UPS SNMP agent; no agent if empty

upsTimeOnBatterySeconds.name: upsTimeOnBatterySeconds
upsTimeOnBatterySeconds.description: Time (in seconds) the UPS is running on battery since power fail (will be cleared on power recovery)

spbbuStatus.name: spbbuStatus
spbbuStatus.description: Status of the service processor's backup battery (not present, OK, recharging)

spbbuDischargeTime.name: spbbuDischargeTime
spbbuDischargeTime.description: Maximum time this backup battery will be discharged, after that a shutdown will be performed (seconds; -1 = unknown)

spbbuTimeOnBatterySeconds.name: spbbuTimeOnBatterySeconds
spbbuTimeOnBatterySeconds.description: Time (in seconds) the backup battery is running on battery since power fail (will be cleared on power recovery)

spbbuDoChargeCycle.name: spbbuDoChargeCycle
spbbuDoChargeCycle.description: Perform a discharge/charge cycle on the backup battery. Reading this object just returns the value 0.

spbbuChargeStatus.name: spbbuChargeStatus
spbbuChargeStatus.description: Reads the current charge level of the rechargeable battery (in percent of the maximum capacity).

interfaceParametersTable.name: interfaceParametersTable
interfaceParametersTable.description: Table with the interface parameters of all management channels, which are controlled by this server.

interfaceParameters.name: interfaceParameters
interfaceParameters.description: The interface parameters of the designated management channel interface.

interfaceCabinetId.name: interfaceCabinetId
interfaceCabinetId.description: CabinetId of the cabinet where the management channel interface resides.

interfaceNumber.name: interfaceNumber
interfaceNumber.description: Index number of the channel management interface (index, 0 based).

interfaceType.name: interfaceType
interfaceType.description: The interface type of the interface.

ipAddress.name: ipAddress
ipAddress.description: The IP v4 address of the interface.

ipAdressNetMask.name: ipAdressNetMask
ipAdressNetMask.description: The IP v4 subnet mask of the interface.

physicalAddress.name: physicalAddress
physicalAddress.description: The interface address of the physical layer of the interface (MAC address).

phoneNumber.name: phoneNumber
phoneNumber.description: The telephone dial number of this interface. Only useful if the interfaceType is of type dial-up(3).

interfaceChannelType.name: interfaceChannelType
interfaceChannelType.description: The managegement channel type of the interface: primary: local operating system interface secondary: local management controller LAN interface management-blade: management blade interface (in a blade server chassis) secondary-remote: remote management controller (in an RSB concentrator environment) secondary-remote-backup: backup remote management controller baseboard-controller: baseboard management controller

dhcpConfigured.name: dhcpConfigured
dhcpConfigured.description: Defines if the ip address should be requested by a dhcp service.

controllerType.name: controllerType
controllerType.description: The type of the remote or baseboard management controller (for identification), like 'RSB', 'RSB S2', 'RSB S2 LP'... These names will not be changed if defined once.

controllerModel.name: controllerModel
controllerModel.description: The model name of the remote management controller (for displaying), like 'Remote Service Board', 'RemoteView Service Board S2'... This name should not be used for identification, only for displaying (can be changed in different firmware versions)!

controllerFWVersion.name: controllerFWVersion
controllerFWVersion.description: The FW version of the remote or baseboard management controller as string;

serviceComponentsTable.name: serviceComponentsTable
serviceComponentsTable.description: Table with the components attached to the service processor

serviceComponents.name: serviceComponents
serviceComponents.description: The components attached to the service processor

serviceComponentProcessorId.name: serviceComponentProcessorId
serviceComponentProcessorId.description: Id of the service processor this component is attached to (index, 0 based)

serviceComponentId.name: serviceComponentId
serviceComponentId.description: Index number of the service component (index, 0 based)

serviceComponentName.name: serviceComponentName
serviceComponentName.description: The name of the component in human readable form

serviceComponentType.name: serviceComponentType
serviceComponentType.description: The type of the componen we are dealing with.

serviceComponentStatus.name: serviceComponentStatus
serviceComponentStatus.description: Describes the status of the component managed by the service processor. Degraded means that some problems have occurred. Error that the component has reported an error that prevents the component form working. Failed means that the component is no longer reacting to the agents requests.

channelType.name: channelType
channelType.description: The managegement channel type of the currently used management channel.

sendTestTrap.name: sendTestTrap
sendTestTrap.description: Send a trap to the manager application(s) to test connection and trap configuration; trap cannot be disabled. Reading this object just returns the value 0.

trapServerName.name: trapServerName
trapServerName.description: Name of server the trap occured

trapTime.name: trapTime
trapTime.description: Time the trap occured (in seconds since 01/01/1970 00:00h)

trapCabinetNumber.name: trapCabinetNumber
trapCabinetNumber.description: Number of the cabinet where the trap was generated

trapObjectNumber.name: trapObjectNumber
trapObjectNumber.description: Number of the object that generated the trap (fan, temperature sensor...)

trapString.name: trapString
trapString.description: Additional string to be displayed in the trap text

trapMinutesRemaining.name: trapMinutesRemaining
trapMinutesRemaining.description: The estimated remaining BBU/UPS capacity in minutes. In the current implementation this is the time remaining until the system will shut down.

trapConfigLowBattTime.name: trapConfigLowBattTime
trapConfigLowBattTime.description: The value of trapMinutesRemaining at which a shut down is initiated. In the current implementation this is always 0.

trapNumValue.name: trapNumValue
trapNumValue.description: Additional numeric value to be displayed in the trap text

trapManagementInterfaceNumber.name: trapManagementInterfaceNumber
trapManagementInterfaceNumber.description: The number of the management channel interface.

testTrap.name: testTrap
testTrap.description: Test trap to verify trap connection.

tempOk.name: tempOk
tempOk.description: The temperature of the indicated sensor has decreased to the normal level.

tempWarn.name: tempWarn
tempWarn.description: The temperature of the indicated sensor has reached the warning level.

tempCritical.name: tempCritical
tempCritical.description: The temperature of the indicated sensor is out of tolerance range. The system will shut down and power off if shutdown is enabled.

trapOnBattery.name: trapOnBattery
trapOnBattery.description: The UPS is operating on battery power or the power supply is drawing current from the backup battery unit (BBU). This status is persistent and is resent at one minute intervals until the mains returns or the system is switched off.

trapOnMains.name: trapOnMains
trapOnMains.description: The mains voltage returned after a power failure.

selftestWarning.name: selftestWarning
selftestWarning.description: Currently the only possible warning is: SCB battery (nearly) empty.

svCommunicationFailure.name: svCommunicationFailure
svCommunicationFailure.description: Communication with the Server Management controller lost.

scbUnconfiguredUPSDetected.name: scbUnconfiguredUPSDetected
scbUnconfiguredUPSDetected.description: A UPS has been detected, but no UPS is configured. This trap will be repeated every 60 minutes until the condition is removed.

scbUPSNotdetected.name: scbUPSNotdetected
scbUPSNotdetected.description: A UPS is configured, but no UPS has been detected. This trap will be repeated every 60 minutes until the condition is removed.

scbUnconfiguredBBUDetected.name: scbUnconfiguredBBUDetected
scbUnconfiguredBBUDetected.description: A BBU has been detected, but no BBU is configured. This trap will be repeated every 60 minutes until the condition is removed.

scbBBUNotdetected.name: scbBBUNotdetected
scbBBUNotdetected.description: A BBU is configured, but no BBU has been detected. This trap will be repeated every 60 minutes until the condition is removed.

notEnoughCabinets.name: notEnoughCabinets
notEnoughCabinets.description: One or more storage extensions missing.

tooManyCabinets.name: tooManyCabinets
tooManyCabinets.description: The actual number of storage extensions is higher than the configured number.

cabinetSwitchedOff.name: cabinetSwitchedOff
cabinetSwitchedOff.description: The cabinet has been switched off.

cabinetSwitchedOn.name: cabinetSwitchedOn
cabinetSwitchedOn.description: The cabinet has been switched on.

internalError.name: internalError
internalError.description: The agent has detected an internal error.

serverShutdown.name: serverShutdown
serverShutdown.description: The server is being shut down.

cabinetNotConfigured.name: cabinetNotConfigured
cabinetNotConfigured.description: The agent has detected a mismatch in the configuration of the server.

powerSupplyRemoved.name: powerSupplyRemoved
powerSupplyRemoved.description: One hot-replace power supply was removed.

powerSupplyAdded.name: powerSupplyAdded
powerSupplyAdded.description: One hot-replace power supply was added.

powerSupplyStatusCritical.name: powerSupplyStatusCritical
powerSupplyStatusCritical.description: Power supply status has become critical.

fanOk.name: fanOk
fanOk.description: The indicated fan is OK again.

tempSensorBroken.name: tempSensorBroken
tempSensorBroken.description: The indicated temperature sensor is broken.

serverManagementDisabled.name: serverManagementDisabled
serverManagementDisabled.description: The server management BIOS is disabled.

trapAcFail.name: trapAcFail
trapAcFail.description: Mains failed in the specified cabinet. This can only happen in storage extension cabinets without UPS or BBU. A server will not have time to send this event.

trapDuplicateCabinetId.name: trapDuplicateCabinetId
trapDuplicateCabinetId.description: Two ore more cabinets (server or storage extension) have the same ID number. The system will not run properly.

trapEventLog.name: trapEventLog
trapEventLog.description: An error message was written into the systemboard's event/error log. This could have happened when an error occured before the agent was running or any error without a specific event message. See server management event/error log for detailed error description.

tempSensorOk.name: tempSensorOk
tempSensorOk.description: The indicated broken temperature sensor is OK again.

svCommunicationEstablished.name: svCommunicationEstablished
svCommunicationEstablished.description: Communication with the Server Management controller established again.

correctableMemErrorAddr.name: correctableMemErrorAddr
correctableMemErrorAddr.description: A correctable memory error at specified address was detected.

uncorrectableMemErrorAddr.name: uncorrectableMemErrorAddr
uncorrectableMemErrorAddr.description: An uncorrectable memory error at specified address was detected.

correctableMemErrorBank.name: correctableMemErrorBank
correctableMemErrorBank.description: A correctable memory error at specified bank was detected.

uncorrectableMemErrorBank.name: uncorrectableMemErrorBank
uncorrectableMemErrorBank.description: An uncorrectable memory error at specified bank was detected.

correctableMemErrorModule.name: correctableMemErrorModule
correctableMemErrorModule.description: A correctable memory error at specified module was detected.

uncorrectableMemErrorModule.name: uncorrectableMemErrorModule
uncorrectableMemErrorModule.description: An uncorrectable memory error at specified module was detected.

correctableMemError.name: correctableMemError
correctableMemError.description: A correctable memory error at unknown address was detected.

uncorrectableMemError.name: uncorrectableMemError
uncorrectableMemError.description: An uncorrectable memory error at unknown address was detected.

powerOffTimeReached.name: powerOffTimeReached
powerOffTimeReached.description: The power-off time is reached! System will shutdown in after delay.

frontDoorStatusChanged.name: frontDoorStatusChanged
frontDoorStatusChanged.description: The front door status has changed.

housingOpenStatusChanged.name: housingOpenStatusChanged
housingOpenStatusChanged.description: The housing open status has changed

sniScRedundantPowerSupplyFailed.name: sniScRedundantPowerSupplyFailed
sniScRedundantPowerSupplyFailed.description: One redundant hot-replace power supply failed.

sniScVoltageOk.name: sniScVoltageOk
sniScVoltageOk.description: Power supply voltage is within normal range again.

sniScVoltageTooLow.name: sniScVoltageTooLow
sniScVoltageTooLow.description: Power supply voltage is too low.

sniScVoltageTooHigh.name: sniScVoltageTooHigh
sniScVoltageTooHigh.description: Power supply voltage is too high.

sniScFanAdded.name: sniScFanAdded
sniScFanAdded.description: The indicated hot-plug fan was inserted.

sniScFanRemoved.name: sniScFanRemoved
sniScFanRemoved.description: The indicated hot-plug fan was removed.

sniScShutdownCancelled.name: sniScShutdownCancelled
sniScShutdownCancelled.description: This event will be sent if a pending server shutdown has been cancelled by the user.

sniScCpuSpeedChanged.name: sniScCpuSpeedChanged
sniScCpuSpeedChanged.description: The CPU clock frequency has been reduced because of a temperature problem.

sieScPowerOn.name: sieScPowerOn
sieScPowerOn.description: The server has been powered on.

sieScNoBootCpu.name: sieScNoBootCpu
sieScNoBootCpu.description: The system boot failed because no valid boot CPU has been found.

sieScPostError.name: sieScPostError
sieScPostError.description: This trap will be sent when the system boot fails, because the power on selftest (POST) has reported an error.

sieScSetupEntered.name: sieScSetupEntered
sieScSetupEntered.description: This trap will be sent when the bios setup has been entered.

sieScBootError.name: sieScBootError
sieScBootError.description: This trap will be sent when no bootable operating system can be found.

sieScBootWatchdogExpired.name: sieScBootWatchdogExpired
sieScBootWatchdogExpired.description: This trap will be sent when the boot watchdog expires.

sieScSoftwareWatchdogExpired.name: sieScSoftwareWatchdogExpired
sieScSoftwareWatchdogExpired.description: This trap will be sent when the software watchdog expires.

sieScUserAuthenticationFailure.name: sieScUserAuthenticationFailure
sieScUserAuthenticationFailure.description: This trap will be sent when an user authentication failure is detected via PPP, FTP, HTTP or telnet fails.

sieScDiagnosticBoot.name: sieScDiagnosticBoot
sieScDiagnosticBoot.description: This trap will be sent when a server is reset and diagnostic boot is enabled. The value in trapString specifies the primary channel i.e. the server name (from which the primary IP address may be derived).

sieScBootRetryCountZero.name: sieScBootRetryCountZero
sieScBootRetryCountZero.description: This trap will be sent when a boot retry counter gets zero on power up

sieScMessageLogFull.name: sieScMessageLogFull
sieScMessageLogFull.description: The System Event Log is full. No more messages can be logged. This trap will not occur on wrap-around log types.

memErrorModulePrefailure.name: memErrorModulePrefailure
memErrorModulePrefailure.description: A memory module is predicted to fail (prefailure).

memErrorModuleReplaced.name: memErrorModuleReplaced
memErrorModuleReplaced.description: A memory module had failed and was replaced by a hot-spare module.

sniScPowerSupplyRedundancyLost.name: sniScPowerSupplyRedundancyLost
sniScPowerSupplyRedundancyLost.description: Power supply redundancy no longer available.

sieScMessageLogWarning.name: sieScMessageLogWarning
sieScMessageLogWarning.description: The warning threshold for the number of System Event Log entries has been exceeded.

sieScCpuPrefailure.name: sieScCpuPrefailure
sieScCpuPrefailure.description: A CPU is predicted to fail (prefailure).

sieScPowerFail.name: sieScPowerFail
sieScPowerFail.description: DC power failed in the specified cabinet. This is the result of the system's power-good sensor monitoring. The system may stop when this condition occurs.

sieScBiosSelftestError.name: sieScBiosSelftestError
sieScBiosSelftestError.description: A critical error happend while BIOS selftest. This error needs to be acknowledged to clear the error condition.

sieScBiosSelftestWatchdogExpired.name: sieScBiosSelftestWatchdogExpired
sieScBiosSelftestWatchdogExpired.description: This trap will be sent when the BIOS selftest watchdog expires. This watchdog expires when the BIOS selftest cannot be finished in a certain time period.

sniScVoltageFailure.name: sniScVoltageFailure
sniScVoltageFailure.description: Power supply voltage is out of range.
